list.item:
(See Guest List attached)Attached but
                                    not printed. The dinner guests from the French side included
                                        Sauvagnargues;
                                    Geoffroy de Courcel, Secretary General of the Quai d’Orsay;
                                    Claude-Pierre Brossolette, Secretary General of the Elysée;
                                    Serge Boidevaix, Chef de Cabinet for the Prime Minister; Maurice
                                    Ulrich, Director de Cabinet of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs;
                                    and Raoul Delay, Director of Information and Press Services at
                                    the Quai d’Orsay. The dinner guests from the American side
                                    included Kissinger,
                                        Irwin, Sonnenfeldt, Hartman, and Ambassador
                                        Robert Anderson, Special Assistant to
                                    the Secretary of State for Press Relations.
